This paper focuses on improving pedestrian detection in crowded scenes by utilizing semantic head information. Therefore, it is most likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of weak annotations and self-supervised learning, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also explores the alignment structure between head and body, which is relevant to robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on a pedestrian detection dataset, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
